  "text": "The xDS configuration flow from control plane to Envoy data plane follows this path:\n\n1. **Protocol Definition (data-plane-api)**: The AggregatedDiscoveryService is defined in envoy/service/discovery/v3/ads.proto with two streaming RPCs:\n   - StreamAggregatedResources(stream DiscoveryRequest) returns (stream DiscoveryResponse)\n   - DeltaAggregatedResources(stream DeltaDiscoveryRequest) returns (stream DeltaDiscoveryResponse)\n   \n   The DiscoveryRequest and DiscoveryResponse message types are defined in envoy/service/discovery/v3/discovery.proto. DiscoveryRequest contains the node identifier, resource names, type_url, version_info, and response_nonce for ACK/NACK. DiscoveryResponse contains the version_info, resources (as google.protobuf.Any), type_url, and nonce for acknowledgment.\n\n2. **Control Plane Implementation (go-control-plane)**: The gRPC server implementation in pkg/server/v3/server.go implements the StreamAggregatedResources handler (line 190). This handler receives DiscoveryRequest messages from Envoy clients and responds with DiscoveryResponse updates. The server interface includes discovery.AggregatedDiscoveryServiceServer which defines these RPC methods. The generated protobuf files (envoy/service/discovery/v3/discovery.pb.go and ads.pb.go) define the DiscoveryRequest (line 203) and DiscoveryResponse (line 335) types used in the gRPC communication.\n\n3. **Data Plane Client Implementation (envoy)**: On the Envoy side, the xDS client implementation centers around GrpcSubscriptionImpl (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_subscription_impl.h), which implements the Subscription interface. This class acts as an adapter from typed subscriptions to the untyped GrpcMux. It initiates the streaming connection, sends DiscoveryRequest messages to subscribe to resources, and handles DiscoveryResponse messages containing configuration updates.\n   \n   The configuration updates flow through ConfigSubscriptionCommonBase (source/common/config/config_provider_impl.h), which provides the framework for managing dynamic configuration. ConfigSubscriptionInstance (for full state-of-the-world xDS) and DeltaConfigSubscriptionInstance (for delta xDS) derive from ConfigSubscriptionCommonBase and manage the subscription lifecycle, apply configuration updates to worker threads, and ensure consistent configuration across the data plane.\n\nThe complete flow: Control plane defines protocol in .proto files → generates Go bindings → xDS server handles client requests via StreamAggregatedResources → Envoy client initiates subscription via GrpcSubscriptionImpl → receives updates via streaming DiscoveryResponse → applies config updates through ConfigSubscriptionInstance to worker threads."
}

